{"key":"processedPost-8853693","value":{"id":8853693,"first":8853612,"last":9034787,"when":1220146859,"utime":"08/31/08 04:40 AM","content":"You want some evaporation, because evaporation of moisture from a substrate or casing layer is also a major pinning trigger.&nbsp; The goal is to allow moisture to evaporate for a few hours, and then to replace that moisture just until the surface glistens, and then to dry out slightly again for a few hours before repeating the process.&nbsp; That cycle is what you're looking for.&nbsp; Just tweak your timers until you achieve the above.<br />RR","title":"Re: What If I could keep Rh up high enough witht he lid off?"}}